# Blog Image Formatter

When processing markdown blog posts, replace all markdown image references with centered HTML image tags.

## Transformation

`![png](<PATH>)` and `![svg](<PATH>)` become:

```html
<center>
  <img src="/images/<PATH>" style="width: 800px;"/>
</center>
```

The `<PATH>` follows the pattern `<BLOG_NAME>_files/<IMAGE_NAME>.png` or `<BLOG_NAME>_files/<IMAGE_NAME>.svg`.

## Example

Before:

```markdown
![png](bayesian_power_ab_testing_files/bayesian_power_ab_testing_5_0.png)
```

After:

```html
<center>
  <img src="/images/bayesian_power_ab_testing_files/bayesian_power_ab_testing_5_0.png" style="width: 800px;"/>
</center>
```

Apply this to every `![png](...)` and `![svg](...)` occurrence in the file.
